cytoscape.editor.event
Class NetworkEditEventAdapter

java.lang.Object
  PBasicInputEventHandler
      cytoscape.editor.event.NetworkEditEventAdapter
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.util.EventListener
Direct Known Subclasses:
BasicNetworkEditEventHandler
public class NetworkEditEventAdapter
extends PBasicInputEventHandler
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener

The NetworkEditEventAdapter class provides stub methods for specialized network edit event handlers, as part of the graph editing framework. The specialized network edit event handler is the key class in the Cytoscape editor for defining the behavior of the editor. The behavior is defined in terms of how the event handler responds to mouse events, drag/drop events, and button press events. All editors must include a network edit event handler class that extends the NetworkEditEventAdapter class.
